div1.p:
Territory of Washington, County of King,
In thendistrict court holding terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of C. I. H. Smith Thomas Kerst
For a writ of Habeas Corpus.

Upong reading and filing the petition Thoams Kerst C H Smithduly signed and verified by him whereby it appears that he is illegaly imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by William Cochrane Sheriff of said County of King at the County Jail in the said County of King in the Territory of Washington and stating wherein the alleged illegality consists from which it appears to be that a writ of Habeas Corpus issue out of and under the seal of the district court of the County of King and Territory of Washington directed to the said William Cochrane Sheriff of said County commanding himto have the body of the said Thoams Kerst C H Smith before me in the court room of the said court at the County of King on the 9 day of Feb 1889 at 4 o'clock P.M. of that day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said petitioner together with the time and cause of his detention, and that you have then and there the said writ.

No 6550
In the Matter of the application of I H Smith for a Writ of Habeas Corpus

FUILED FEB 9 1889 W E Ledgerwood Clerk.
Osborn & Dyer. ATTORNEYS for Petitioner ROOMS 17 and 13 YESLER BLK. SEATTLE W. T.
